  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I spoke to him once when I-- when he interrogated me and put me through the [? wall ?] and said he would make me a second belly button or a second [? asshole. ?] And then when he came and said, [NON-ENGLISH], [INAUDIBLE] transport [? you ?] [? out. ?] And then I spoke to him over the-- there were two [? personal ?] [? contacts. ?] There was only two personal, very short contacts.",
      "word_count": 76
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then I had two telephone contacts, when I called him from-- spoke to him.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't remember how I came to speak to him.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I called him from-- from Arnoldstein when his train was stuck there and threatened him with [? the ?] [? masada ?] [? repetition. ?] And then when I spoke to him from Romania, which ended with, we'll still-- we'll-- we'll still get you, Perl.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Well, I ?] had two personal-- very short personal contacts and two very short telephone contacts.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I was called to the Eichmann trial at the invitation of Hausner, who was the-- who was the chief-- chief prosecutor.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And-- and he wanted to interview me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He wanted to have me ready for the case that Eichmann should say that he cooperated in the rescue of so many Jews because all this wouldn't have done without-- been done without his help.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But I knew that he had to be forced by-- by-- by higher up.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So when I was there, waiting to be called possibly, well, while-- while still the defense was still on, his lawyer, Servatius, had heard that I am here and I'm alive.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Was not a usual thing for a Jew who [INAUDIBLE] around in Europe at that time.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
